properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic will be switched on the new Parkes Bypass from Tuesday 15 April.

Access to Bogan Road northbound is from the Parkes Bypass only.

Bogan Road northbound between the bypass and existing Newell Hwy will be closed (access southbound from bypass only).

The existing Newell Highway will be closed between Currajong Rest Area and Maguire Road.

At the completion of the access works, both the current Newell Highway and the new Bypass will be open to traffic.

Northbound traffic on Henry Lawson Drive will be split due to ongoing roadworks.

  • If you're turning left onto Newbridge Road, use the left lanes where the road splits.
  • If you're going straight or turning right, stay in the right lanes where the road splits.

Changes to traffic conditions will be in place on the Sydney Harbour Bridge at various times while the bridge and other infrastructure are being upgraded and maintained. These changes include a combination of lane closures and speed reductions.

At least one lane will be maintained in each direction during work hours.

arrangementElements.html:
The OSOM route will be the new Parkes Bypass.

OSOM vehicles travelling east from the Newell Highway will take the new Parkes Bypass to the Condobolin Road roundabout (exit west) and travel via the new alignment of Hartigan Avenue.

The rest area adjacent to Saleyards Rd will be closed. Access will be returned after 6 weeks. For more information on available Rest Areas visit the Rest Areas Map.
